      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEASIDE BOY (1) is a progressive three-year-old who was too good when resuming at Maryborough last week, leading to score by 5m. Fitter for that and has the gate speed to take advantage of the inside draw so can go on with it. LAMBRO MACH (4) looks close to a win after placing in all three starts off a let-up, last time coming wider on the back line for a 2.8m third at Melton. Better suited on the front row and won his lone attempt at this circuit and distance. HEATSEEKER (7) led in a higher-graded race last start and boxed on to go under by 2.5m. Won two in a row prior and while he draws deep he won the only time he attempted this distance. KISS ME MINI NZ (6) worked when midfield last time but has won a trial since and overcame a back row draw to score two back at Melton. Player.",
